      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Read all safety warnings and instructions before use.</strong> Failure
        to follow the warnings and instructions may result in electric shock, fire, and/or
        serious injury. Save all warnings and instructions for future reference.
      </div>

      <h3>Required Personal Protective Equipment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Face mask</li>
        <li>Safety gloves</li>
        <li>Ear protection</li>
        <li>Safety glasses</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Work Area &amp; Electrical Safety</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Keep the work area clean and well lit. Cluttered or dark areas invite accidents.</li>
        <li>Do not operate in explosive atmospheres or near flammable liquids, gases, or dust.</li>
        <li>Keep children and bystanders away while operating the tool.</li>
        <li>The plug must match the outlet. Never modify the plug; do not use adapter plugs with grounded tools.</li>
        <li>Avoid body contact with grounded surfaces (pipes, radiators, ranges, refrigerators).</li>
        <li>Do not expose the tool to rain or wet conditions.</li>
        <li>Do not abuse the cord &mdash; never use it to carry, pull, or unplug the tool. Keep it away from heat, oil, sharp edges, and moving parts.</li>
        <li>Outdoors, use an extension cord rated for outdoor use. In damp locations, use a residual current device (RCD) protected supply.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Personal Safety &amp; Tool Care</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Stay alert. Do not use while tired or under the influence of drugs, alcohol, or medication.</li>
        <li>Always wear eye protection and appropriate PPE.</li>
        <li>Prevent unintentional starting &mdash; ensure the switch is off before connecting to power.</li>
        <li>Do not overreach; keep proper footing and balance. The sander can develop a torque reaction when started.</li>
        <li>Dress properly. No loose clothing or jewelry. Keep hair, clothing, and gloves away from moving parts.</li>
        <li>Connect and use dust extraction whenever it is provided.</li>
        <li>Do not overload the tool, and do not use it if the switch fails to turn it on and off.</li>
        <li>Disconnect the plug before adjustments, accessory changes, or storage. Store idle tools out of reach of children.</li>
        <li>Maintain the tool; check for misalignment, binding, or breakage. Keep handles dry, clean, and grease-free.</li>
        <li>Have the tool serviced only by a qualified repair person using identical replacement parts.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Additional Warnings</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Tool safety is granted only by using original Mirka backing pads.</li>
        <li>Read the Material Safety Data Sheet (MSDS) for the work surface.</li>
        <li>If hand or wrist discomfort is experienced, stop working and seek medical attention. Repetitive motion and vibration overexposure can cause injury.</li>
        <li>The power socket and connector are non-IEC couplers &mdash; use only an original Mirka power supply cable. Replace a damaged cable with a Mirka original.</li>
        <li>Check the tool, backing pad, power cord, and fittings regularly for wear.</li>
        <li>Clean or replace the dust extractor collection bag daily. Dust can be highly combustible.</li>
        <li>Always ensure the workpiece is firmly fixed in place, and keep hands clear of the spinning accessory.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Dust hazard:</strong> Some dust created by power sanding contains chemicals
        known to cause cancer, birth defects, or other reproductive harm &mdash; for example
        lead from lead-based paints, crystalline silica from masonry, and arsenic and chromium
        from chemically treated lumber. Work in a well-ventilated area and use approved dust
        masks designed to filter microscopic particles.
      </div>

      <h2>Components &amp; Controls</h2>
      <p>
        All controls sit on the top of the sander. The on/off key powers the electronics,
        the lever starts the motor and varies speed, and the speed&nbsp;+ / speed&minus;
        buttons set the maximum RPM. The LED bar shows the current speed step, the
        multi-purpose LED reports status, and the wireless indication LED shows Bluetooth
        state.
      </p>
