        <img src="/manuals/mirka-deos-343x/p03_01.jpg" alt="Mirka DEOS II 343X orbital sander showing the power cord, top control panel with speed and on/off buttons, palm grip, and 3.0 mm orbit rectangular backing pad" />
        <figcaption>Figure 1 &mdash; Mirka DEOS II 343X with power cord, control panel, and 75 &times; 100 mm backing pad (the &ldquo;3.0&rdquo; marking denotes the 3.0&nbsp;mm orbit)</figcaption>
      </div>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/mirka-deos-343x/p03_00.png" alt="Top view of the DEOS II control panel showing the on/off power button, LED speed bar, speed minus and speed plus buttons, and the warning and compliance symbols" />
        <figcaption>Control panel: on/off key, LED speed bar, speed&minus; / speed+ buttons, and compliance markings</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>When unpacking, confirm the tool is intact, complete, and undamaged in transit. Never use a damaged tool.</li>
        <li>Check that the backing pad is correctly attached and tightened.</li>
        <li>Connect the power cord to the tool, then to a grounded outlet (110 VAC, 50&ndash;60 Hz).</li>
        <li>For maximum performance, pair the sander with a Mirka dust extractor and Mirka net abrasives &mdash; the basis of Mirka dust-free sanding. Connecting the tool's cord to the extractor's outlet enables the extractor autostart function.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Operation</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Make sure the sander is switched off. Select a suitable abrasive and center it on the backing pad.</li>
        <li>Press the On/Off key. The multi-purpose LED flashes green to show the tool is ready.</li>
        <li>Press the lever to start the sander. Adjust speed between 5,000 RPM and the set maximum by changing the lever position.</li>
        <li>Set the maximum RPM with speed+ / speed&minus;. Steps are 5,000, 6,000, 7,000, 7,500, 8,000, 9,000, and 10,000 RPM.</li>
        <li>The tool has two speed-control modes: a default linear mode (speed follows the lever) and a fixed mode (speed stays at the set maximum while running). Press speed+ and speed&minus; simultaneously to toggle between them.</li>
        <li>Always place the tool on the work surface before starting it, and remove it from the surface before stopping.</li>
        <li>When finished, press the On/Off key to turn the sander off. All LEDs turn off except the wireless indication LED if the tool is connected.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Bluetooth &amp; MyMirka</h3>
      <p>
        The DEOS II uses Bluetooth&reg; Low Energy and connects to the MyMirka app for
        additional functionality (RF 2402&ndash;2480 MHz). To activate: connect the power
        cord to mains, then press and hold the Speed+ button while switching the tool on
        with the On/Off button. The wireless indication LED blinks blue, then turns solid
        once connected. Bluetooth deactivates when the tool is unplugged. Do not activate
        Bluetooth if the app is not installed or not available in your country.
      </p>
      <div class="note">
        This device complies with FCC Part 15 (Class B) and Industry Canada licence-exempt
        RSS. Operation is subject to two conditions: (1) it may not cause harmful
        interference, and (2) it must accept any interference received, including
        interference that may cause undesired operation. Changes or modifications not
        expressly approved by Mirka could void your authority to operate the equipment.
      </div>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>
      <div class="warning">
        Always disconnect the power before maintenance. Use only original Mirka spare parts.
      </div>

      <h3>Replacing the Backing Pad</h3>
      <p>
        Screws are sized A = 8 mm (only present on the 70 &times; 198 mm / 383X pad) and
        B = 16 mm. On the 343X, remove the four pad screws to free the pad.
      </p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/mirka-deos-343x/p16_01.png" alt="Exploded diagram of the DEOS II backing pad mounting showing the pad screw locations labeled A and B on the rectangular backing plate" />
        <figcaption>Backing pad mounting &mdash; screw positions A (8 mm) and B (16 mm)</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Remove:</strong> Turn the tool upside down, remove the four A screws, then the four B screws, and lift off the backing pad.</li>
        <li><strong>Install:</strong> Fit the new pad, start the four B screws, then the four A screws, and finally tighten all screws.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Pad Saver</h3>
      <p>
        Mirka pad savers sit between the backing pad and the sanding disc to protect the pad
        when sanding aggressively and continuously with net products. Change them regularly
        to prolong backing-pad life.
      </p>

