      <h3>Further Service</h3>
      <p>
        Servicing must always be performed by trained personnel. To keep the warranty valid
        and ensure optimal safety and function, have service carried out by a Mirka
        authorized service centre. Repairs by a non-authorized repairer will breach the Mirka
        warranty; electrical tools must be serviced in accordance with national requirements.
      </p>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-purpose LED flashes between red and green</td>
            <td>Connected to a mains outlet with the wrong voltage</td>
            <td>Connect to an outlet matching the tool's nominal voltage (100&ndash;120 VAC)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>No light from the multi-purpose LED when switched on</td>
            <td>Power cord not properly attached to the tool or mains socket</td>
            <td>Connect the power cord properly at both ends</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-purpose LED is red and the tool slows to minimum speed while sanding</td>
            <td>Temperature too high; too heavy long-term load</td>
            <td>Reduce the load for a while &mdash; the tool will speed up again</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-purpose LED is red and RPM is slightly reduced</td>
            <td>Too heavy short-term load</td>
            <td>Use a lighter load; the LED will automatically return to green</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Brake seal does not work (not applicable to DEOS 343)</td>
            <td>Worn brake seal or damaged spindle bearing</td>
            <td>Check and replace the brake seal or spindle bearing if necessary</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tool has stopped and the multi-purpose LED is red</td>
            <td>Safety mode due to high temperature</td>
            <td>Wait until the tool has cooled down</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Disposal</h2>
      <div class="danger">
        Render redundant power tools unusable by removing the power cord. Observe applicable
        country-specific regulations for the disposal and recycling of disused machines,
        packaging, and accessories.
      </div>
      <p>
        EU only: Do not dispose of electric power tools in household waste. Under European
        directives on waste electrical and electronic equipment, end-of-life tools must be
        collected separately and taken to an environmentally compatible recycling facility.
      </p>

